The DA is presenting its updated position on migration and xenophobia at its  Poli-Con 2022. DA head of policy Gwen Ngwenya,  shadow deputy minister of home affairs Adrian Roos, shadow minister of labour Michael Cardo and  caucus media whip Solly Malatsi will   discuss the DA’s migration policy, as ratified by the party’s federal council,  its highest decision-making body. TimesLIVE